<p>New semiconductor device technology enables injection of light-emitting diodes, silicon devices, actuators, and sensors at precisely controlled locations within biological tissues, such as the brain. <bold>Kim <italic>et al.</italic></bold> (p. <related-article related-article-type="in-this-issue" vol="340" issue="6129" page="211">211</related-article>) show how wireless control of animal models using these technologies and the techniques of optogenetics provide new insights into basic behavioral neuroscience.</p>
